1 hour ago, vardicd said:

so I don't know why some bases would show up, but not others?

The bases should all be in their locations with just Kerbin Side Remastered and Kerbal Konstructs as the only required mods. Some bases are designed to be hidden in career mode but flying over them should trigger their discovery. 

I'd check your ksp.log to see if there are any issues with those two mods during game load or any conflicts with other mods you might have. You may want to test with a clean install and only those two mods and see if it loads correctly. Then you could add additional mods and test that it is still working. 

I have run into some issues with bases being malformed, but I found that changing terrain detail in settings to default cleared those up.

Also it seems like Kerbin Side Remastered doesn't like it if you alter your planet size as the location of the statics can change.  I play on the default Kerbin size.

Caveat: All that said, I'm not a expert with either of these mods... I just write flight contract packs for them.
